source: crates/cli/tests/cli_comprehensive_e2e_tests.rs
expression: stdout
---
Build a bounded simulator-to-Moza FFB smoke proof from output logs

Usage: wheelctl moza simulator-ffb-smoke [OPTIONS] --lane <LANE> --game <GAME> --output-log-artifact <OUTPUT_LOG_ARTIFACT> --watchdog-timeout-ms <WATCHDOG_TIMEOUT_MS>

Options:
      --json
          Output in JSON format for machine parsing

      --lane <LANE>
          Lane artifact directory, e.g. ci/hardware/moza-r5/2026-05-06

      --game <GAME>
          Simulator or bridge name

  -v, --verbose...
          Verbose logging

      --telemetry-source <TELEMETRY_SOURCE>
          Telemetry source: real_game or simhub_bridge

          [default: simhub_bridge]

      --output-log-artifact <OUTPUT_LOG_ARTIFACT>
          Lane-relative output log artifact

      --strategy <STRATEGY>
          Bounded simulator FFB output strategy

          Possible values:
          - direct-report-0x20:   Moza proprietary direct torque report 0x20
          - pidff-bounded-effect: Standard HID PIDFF bounded effect path

          [default: direct-report-0x20]

      --descriptor-trusted
          Descriptor trust was established before simulator FFB

      --explicit-operator-override
          Explicit operator override allowed direct-mode FFB without descriptor trust

      --watchdog-timeout-ms <WATCHDOG_TIMEOUT_MS>
          Watchdog timeout used during the smoke run

      --stop-cleared-output
          Stop event cleared output

      --pause-cleared-output
          Pause event cleared output

      --game-exit-cleared-output
          Game exit cleared output

      --json-out <JSON_OUT>
          Write the simulator FFB smoke proof receipt to this JSON file

      --overwrite
          Replace an existing proof receipt

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
